Hello Jonathan,

To proceed with reserving the vessel, please find below the list of required documents:

1. Bill of Lading, 1 set;
2. P&I Club certificate, 1 set;
3. A1 Tanker certificate, 1 set;
4. Charter Party, 1 set;
5. Release of any attachments or liabilities and other documents as may be requested by the mortgagee. A mortgagee's consent may be required.
6. Master's account, 1 set;
7. Draft survey, 1 set;
8. Stability Certificate, 1 set;
9. Safety equipment certificates, 1 set;
10. MCA Authorization to use electronic chart display and information system (ECDIS), 1 set;
11. Oil record book, 1 set;
12. Third-party damage report and certificates, 1 set;
13. All maritime papers.

Please ensure these documents are prepared and submitted promptly.

Best regards,
Mr. Liang

Hi Mr. Batra,

May I request you to assist us in exploring with your owners the following options for our shipment as below:

1. Send the 'Coastline' from Kakinada to your discharge port to arrive in 6 days time;
2. Send the 'Coastline' from Kakinada to your discharge port to arrive in 10 days time;
3. Send the 'Sambalino' from your discharge port to the Singapore loading port to arrive in 6 days time;
4. Send the 'Sambalino' from your discharge port to the Singapore loading port to arrive in 10 days time;

As soon as the draft survey is received, I will forward you a copy with the same. In the meantime, if you require further information, please feel free to contact me on the below.

Thanks,
Ernest
